The ESPResSo compilation and installation process 

A detailed installation guide for ESPResSo is found in


QUICK START
-----------
In many cases, once you have obtained the sources, compiling and
running ESPResSo requires only two steps:

> configure
> make
 
When both steps have completed successfully, you can run Espresso with
help of the command

> Espresso

WHEN THIS ISN'T ENOUGH
----------------------
A detailed installation guide that explains the different options of
configure and make can be found in the ESPResSo's User's Guide "ug.pdf"
